  <h2>Layout</h2>
  <p>Layouts require large spacers to create white space and disassociate sections from each other.</p>

  <h3>Applying spacers</h3>
  <p>Every layout or section on a page needs enough vertical spacing so that content doesn’t feel too close or crushed.
  The top and bottom spacing of a layout is 64px by default, but some layouts feature different spacing depending on hierarchy or importance.
  Some components like <a href="{{ '/elements/tabs/' | url }}">Tabs</a> contain a large spacer because there’s a content area layout inside.</p>

  <uxdot-example variant="full">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/spacing/spacing-layouts.svg' | url }}" alt="Spacing within layouts">
  </uxdot-example>

  <h3>Responsive design</h3>
  <p>When layouts reduce in size, the spacers will also reduce in size to compensate for the loss in screen real estate.</p>
